```bash
# Two forms:
name() { command-list; }
function name [()] { command-list; }
```
Define a function that can be called by name. Arguments are accessed as `$1`, `$2`, etc. `$@` for all arguments, `$#` for count. Use `local` for local variables. Use `return [n]` to exit with a status. Functions can be exported with `export -f name`.
